new structure of items classes/variables

Item:
    name
    description
    weight
    value
    sprite name
    inventoriable:boolclass name (db entry, not in the code)
    buffs:dict{Stat:float}
 
Stackable(Item):
    define management and interaction of stack.
    max stack size, how to add a new instance of item if stack is too big and item is added, automatically coalescing 
    stacks in inventory
    

Consumables(stackable))
mark as true in the db "stackable"
    duration

Ammunition(stackable)
mark as true in the db "stackable"
    damage
    destroy_on_use_probability - float

equippables - stackable always set to false
    slots; list of slots
    slot_count; -1 if all slots; other number if fewer than possible slots (one of two hands, for example)
    durability_max - integer that referrs to wear. effectively like HP - not set to 100 uniformly
    durability_current
    render_on_creature - boolean of whether to render item on creature

weapons(equippables)

    damage
    attack_time_ms
    directions - list with values like 'front','front left', 'front right' which are interpreted based on the orientation of the 
        creature wielding the weapon. so if the creature is moving left, then ['front left','front','front right'] would mean 
        the tile to the bottom left, the tile to the left, and the tile to the top left of the creature
        this entails adding a direction to the creature class that changes based on how the 
        creature is moving
    range - integer number of tiles; 1 is typical melee range, 
    ammunition_type - nullable - should be tied to specific stackable ITEMS

